block.p: Holly Anne Winzler, the daughter of Lydia and Robert G. Winzler of Cinnaminson, N.J., was married yesterday to Michael Joseph Mulderig, the son of Teresa S. Mulderig of Mountain Top, Pa., and the late Frank W. Mulderig. The Rev. Gordon L. Huff performed the ceremony at St. Matthew Lutheran Church in Moorestown, N.J.
The couple graduated from the University of Pennsylvania, he cum laude.

Holly Anne Winzler, the daughter of Lydia and Robert G. Winzler of Cinnaminson, N.J., was married yesterday to Michael Joseph Mulderig, the son of Teresa S. Mulderig of Mountain Top, Pa., and the late Frank W. Mulderig. The Rev. Gordon L. Huff performed the ceremony at St. Matthew Lutheran Church in Moorestown, N.J.
The couple graduated from the University of Pennsylvania, he cum laude.

The bride, 34, will continue to use her name professionally. She is a public relations consultant in Moorestown, advising financial and technology companies. The bridegroom, 36, oversees wine selection for the Total Beverage Corporation, a chain of wine retailers based in Rockville, Md.
